{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":897,"text":"So I'm here to talk to you\nabout the walkable city."},{"time":3810,"text":"What is the walkable city?"},{"time":5193,"text":"Well, for want of a better definition,"},{"time":7698,"text":"it's a city in which the car\nis an optional instrument of freedom,"},{"time":14610,"text":"rather than a prosthetic device."},{"time":16518,"text":"And I'd like to talk about\nwhy we need the walkable city,"},{"time":19497,"text":"and I'd like to talk about\nhow to do the walkable city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23679,"text":"Most of the talks I give these days\nare about why we need it,"},{"time":28043,"text":"but you guys are smart."},{"time":32314,"text":"And also I gave that talk\nexactly a month ago,"},{"time":35585,"text":"and you can see it at TED.com."},{"time":37676,"text":"So today I want to talk\nabout how to do it."},{"time":40700,"text":"In a lot of time thinking about this,"},{"time":42663,"text":"I've come up with what I call\nthe general theory of walkability."},{"time":45787,"text":"A bit of a pretentious term,\nit's a little tongue-in-cheek,"},{"time":48741,"text":"but it's something\nI've thought about for a long time,"},{"time":51339,"text":"and I'd like to share\nwhat I think I've figured out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54747,"text":"In the American city,\nthe typical American city --"},{"time":57610,"text":"the typical American city\nis not Washington, DC,"},{"time":59874,"text":"or New York, or San Francisco;"},{"time":62206,"text":"it's Grand Rapids or Cedar\nRapids or Memphis --"},{"time":65477,"text":"in the typical American city\nin which most people own cars"},{"time":68612,"text":"and the temptation\nis to drive them all the time,"},{"time":70957,"text":"if you're going to get them to walk,\nthen you have to offer a walk"},{"time":74760,"text":"that's as good as a drive or better."},{"time":76632,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":77807,"text":"It means you need to offer\nfour things simultaneously:"},{"time":80372,"text":"there needs to be a proper reason to walk,"},{"time":82453,"text":"the walk has to be safe and feel safe,"},{"time":84827,"text":"the walk has to be comfortable"},{"time":86546,"text":"and the walk has to be interesting."},{"time":88339,"text":"You need to do all four\nof these things simultaneously,"},{"time":90973,"text":"and that's the structure of my talk today,"},{"time":93027,"text":"to take you through each of those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94680,"text":"The reason to walk\nis a story I learned from my mentors,"},{"time":97968,"text":"Andr√©s Duany and Elizabeth Plater-Zyberk,"},{"time":100352,"text":"the founders of the New Urbanism movement."},{"time":102377,"text":"And I should say half the slides\nand half of my talk today"},{"time":105914,"text":"I learned from them."},{"time":107264,"text":"It's the story of planning,"},{"time":109067,"text":"the story of the formation\nof the planning profession."},{"time":112331,"text":"When in the 19th century\npeople were choking"},{"time":117106,"text":"from the soot of the dark, satanic mills,"},{"time":119623,"text":"the planners said, hey, let's move\nthe housing away from the mills."},{"time":124023,"text":"And lifespans increased\nimmediately, dramatically,"},{"time":127514,"text":"and we like to say"},{"time":128689,"text":"the planners have been trying to repeat\nthat experience ever since."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131905,"text":"So there's the onset\nof what we call Euclidean zoning,"},{"time":134571,"text":"the separation of the landscape\ninto large areas of single use."},{"time":138670,"text":"And typically when I arrive\nin a city to do a plan,"},{"time":141171,"text":"a plan like this already awaits me\non the property that I'm looking at."},{"time":145234,"text":"And all a plan like this guarantees"},{"time":146960,"text":"is that you will not have a walkable city,"},{"time":149023,"text":"because nothing is located\nnear anything else."},{"time":151967,"text":"The alternative, of course,\nis our most walkable city,"},{"time":155631,"text":"and I like to say, you know,\nthis is a Rothko,"},{"time":158185,"text":"and this is a Seurat."},{"time":159712,"text":"It's just a different way --\nhe was the pointilist --"},{"time":162277,"text":"it's a different way of making places."},{"time":164134,"text":"And even this map of Manhattan\nis a bit misleading"},{"time":166967,"text":"because the red color\nis uses that are mixed vertically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171171,"text":"So this is the big story\nof the New Urbanists --"},{"time":173899,"text":"to acknowledge\nthat there are only two ways"},{"time":176435,"text":"that have been tested by the thousands"},{"time":178749,"text":"to build communities,\nin the world and throughout history."},{"time":181713,"text":"One is the traditional neighborhood."},{"time":183615,"text":"You see here several neighborhoods\nof Newburyport, Massachusetts,"},{"time":187053,"text":"which is defined as being compact\nand being diverse --"},{"time":191344,"text":"places to live, work, shop,\nrecreate, get educated --"},{"time":195510,"text":"all within walking distance."},{"time":197413,"text":"And it's defined as being walkable."},{"time":199573,"text":"There are lots of small streets."},{"time":201131,"text":"Each one is comfortable to walk on."},{"time":202881,"text":"And we contrast that to the other way,"},{"time":205419,"text":"an invention that happened\nafter the Second World War,"},{"time":208262,"text":"suburban sprawl,"},{"time":209544,"text":"clearly not compact, clearly not diverse,\nand it's not walkable,"},{"time":214145,"text":"because so few of the streets connect,"},{"time":216067,"text":"that those streets that do connect\nbecome overburdened,"},{"time":218974,"text":"and you wouldn't let your kid out on them."},{"time":221088,"text":"And I want to thank Alex Maclean,\nthe aerial photographer,"},{"time":223963,"text":"for many of these beautiful pictures\nthat I'm showing you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227042,"text":"So it's fun to break sprawl down\ninto its constituent parts."},{"time":230686,"text":"It's so easy to understand,"},{"time":232287,"text":"the places where you only live,\nthe places where you only work,"},{"time":236144,"text":"the places where you only shop,"},{"time":238124,"text":"and our super-sized public institutions."},{"time":241492,"text":"Schools get bigger and bigger,"},{"time":242956,"text":"and therefore, further\nand further from each other."},{"time":245376,"text":"And the ratio of the size\nof the parking lot"},{"time":248529,"text":"to the size of the school"},{"time":249769,"text":"tells you all you need to know,"},{"time":251409,"text":"which is that no child\nhas ever walked to this school,"},{"time":253971,"text":"no child will ever walk to this school."},{"time":255900,"text":"The seniors and juniors are driving\nthe freshmen and the sophomores,"},{"time":259764,"text":"and of course we have\nthe crash statistics to prove it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262412,"text":"And then the super-sizing\nof our other civic institutions"},{"time":265904,"text":"like playing fields --"},{"time":267098,"text":"it's wonderful that Westin\nin the Ft. Lauderdale area"},{"time":270995,"text":"has eight soccer fields\nand eight baseball diamonds"},{"time":274087,"text":"and 20 tennis courts,"},{"time":275970,"text":"but look at the road\nthat takes you to that location,"},{"time":279606,"text":"and would you let your child bike on it?"},{"time":281576,"text":"And this is why we have\nthe soccer mom now."},{"time":283730,"text":"When I was young, I had one soccer field,"},{"time":285996,"text":"one baseball diamond and one tennis court,"},{"time":288045,"text":"but I could walk to it,\nbecause it was in my neighborhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290927,"text":"Then the final part of sprawl\nthat everyone forgot to count:"},{"time":293802,"text":"if you're going to separate everything\nfrom everything else"},{"time":296646,"text":"and reconnect it\nonly with automotive infrastructure,"},{"time":299204,"text":"then this is what your landscape\nbegins to look like."},{"time":301750,"text":"The main message here is:"},{"time":302989,"text":"if you want to have a walkable city,\nyou can't start with the sprawl model."},{"time":306615,"text":"you need the bones of an urban model."},{"time":308710,"text":"This is the outcome\nof that form of design,"},{"time":311582,"text":"as is this."},{"time":312997,"text":"And this is something\nthat a lot of Americans want."},{"time":315610,"text":"But we have to understand\nit's a two-part American dream."},{"time":318347,"text":"If you're dreaming for this,"},{"time":319731,"text":"you're also going to be dreaming of this,\noften to absurd extremes,"},{"time":323136,"text":"when we build our landscape\nto accommodate cars first."},{"time":325777,"text":"And the experience\nof being in these places --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328042,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329083,"text":"This is not Photoshopped."},{"time":330487,"text":"Walter Kulash took this slide."},{"time":332513,"text":"It's in Panama City."},{"time":334234,"text":"This is a real place."},{"time":336047,"text":"And being a driver\ncan be a bit of a nuisance,"},{"time":338550,"text":"and being a pedestrian\ncan be a bit of a nuisance"},{"time":341039,"text":"in these places."},{"time":342564,"text":"This is a slide that epidemiologists\nhave been showing for some time now,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346062,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":347102,"text":"The fact that we have a society\nwhere you drive to the parking lot"},{"time":350591,"text":"to take the escalator to the treadmill"},{"time":352489,"text":"shows that we're doing something wrong."},{"time":354441,"text":"But we know how to do it better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356037,"text":"Here are the two models contrasted."},{"time":357744,"text":"I show this slide,"},{"time":358923,"text":"which has been a formative document\nof the New Urbanism now"},{"time":361733,"text":"for almost 30 years,"},{"time":363161,"text":"to show that sprawl and the traditional\nneighborhood contain the same things."},{"time":367344,"text":"It's just how big are they,"},{"time":368754,"text":"how close are they to each other,"},{"time":370377,"text":"how are they interspersed together"},{"time":372076,"text":"and do you have a street network,\nrather than a cul-de-sac"},{"time":375017,"text":"or a collector system of streets?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377076,"text":"So when we look at a downtown area,"},{"time":378917,"text":"at a place that has a hope\nof being walkable,"},{"time":381076,"text":"and mostly that's our downtowns\nin America's cities"},{"time":383658,"text":"and towns and villages,"},{"time":385450,"text":"we look at them and say\nwe want the proper balance of uses."},{"time":388539,"text":"So what is missing or underrepresented?"},{"time":390698,"text":"And again, in the typical American cities\nin which most Americans live,"},{"time":394382,"text":"it is housing that is lacking."},{"time":396416,"text":"The jobs-to-housing balance is off."},{"time":398630,"text":"And you find that when\nyou bring housing back,"},{"time":400837,"text":"these other things start to come back too,"},{"time":402927,"text":"and housing is usually first\namong those things."},{"time":405427,"text":"And, of course, the thing\nthat shows up last and eventually"},{"time":408555,"text":"is the schools,"},{"time":409760,"text":"because the people have to move in,"},{"time":412104,"text":"the young pioneers have to move in,\nget older, have kids"},{"time":416949,"text":"and fight, and then the schools\nget pretty good eventually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420011,"text":"The other part of this part,"},{"time":422337,"text":"the useful city part,"},{"time":425852,"text":"is transit,"},{"time":427181,"text":"and you can have a perfectly\nwalkable neighborhood without it."},{"time":430570,"text":"But perfectly walkable cities\nrequire transit,"},{"time":433899,"text":"because if you don't have access\nto the whole city as a pedestrian,"},{"time":437364,"text":"then you get a car,"},{"time":438549,"text":"and if you get a car,"},{"time":439728,"text":"the city begins to reshape itself\naround your needs,"},{"time":442300,"text":"and the streets get wider\nand the parking lots get bigger"},{"time":445006,"text":"and you no longer have a walkable city."},{"time":446907,"text":"So transit is essential."},{"time":448086,"text":"But every transit experience,\nevery transit trip,"},{"time":450511,"text":"begins or ends as a walk,"},{"time":452430,"text":"and so we have to remember to build\nwalkability around our transit stations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456252,"text":"Next category, the biggest one,\nis the safe walk."},{"time":459021,"text":"It's what most walkability\nexperts talk about."},{"time":461261,"text":"It is essential, but alone not enough\nto get people to walk."},{"time":465326,"text":"And there are so many moving parts\nthat add up to a walkable city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468493,"text":"The first is block size."},{"time":470093,"text":"This is Portland, Oregon,"},{"time":471464,"text":"famously 200-foot blocks,\nfamously walkable."},{"time":475054,"text":"This is Salt Lake City,"},{"time":476396,"text":"famously 600-foot blocks,"},{"time":478500,"text":"famously unwalkable."},{"time":479893,"text":"If you look at the two,\nit's almost like two different planets,"},{"time":482923,"text":"but these places were both built by humans"},{"time":485263,"text":"and in fact, the story is that when\nyou have a 200-foot block city,"},{"time":488927,"text":"you can have a two-lane city,"},{"time":490485,"text":"or a two-to-four lane city,"},{"time":491926,"text":"and a 600-foot block city\nis a six-lane city, and that's a problem."},{"time":495975,"text":"These are the crash statistics."},{"time":497477,"text":"When you double the block size --"},{"time":499587,"text":"this was a study\nof 24 California cities --"},{"time":501644,"text":"when you double the block size,"},{"time":503160,"text":"you almost quadruple\nthe number of fatal accidents"},{"time":506810,"text":"on non-highway streets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508835,"text":"So how many lanes do we have?"},{"time":511090,"text":"This is where I'm going to tell you\nwhat I tell every audience I meet,"},{"time":514591,"text":"which is to remind you\nabout induced demand."},{"time":517345,"text":"Induced demand applies\nboth to highways and to city streets."},{"time":521806,"text":"And induced demand tells us\nthat when we widen the streets"},{"time":525315,"text":"to accept the congestion\nthat we're anticipating,"},{"time":528437,"text":"or the additional trips\nthat we're anticipating"},{"time":530798,"text":"in congested systems,\nit is principally that congestion"},{"time":534735,"text":"that is constraining demand,"},{"time":536752,"text":"and so that the widening comes,"},{"time":538538,"text":"and there are all of these latent trips\nthat are ready to happen."},{"time":541678,"text":"People move further from work"},{"time":543091,"text":"and make other choices\nabout when they commute,"},{"time":545348,"text":"and those lanes fill up\nvery quickly with traffic,"},{"time":547746,"text":"so we widen the street again,\nand they fill up again."},{"time":550271,"text":"And we've learned that\nin congested systems,"},{"time":552521,"text":"we cannot satisfy the automobile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554960,"text":"This is from Newsweek Magazine --\nhardly an esoteric publication:"},{"time":558434,"text":"\"Today's engineers acknowledge"},{"time":560126,"text":"that building new roads\nusually makes traffic worse.\""},{"time":563376,"text":"My response to reading this was,\nmay I please meet some of these engineers,"},{"time":566963,"text":"because these are not the ones that I --"},{"time":569053,"text":"there are great exceptions\nthat I'm working with now --"},{"time":571667,"text":"but these are not the engineers\none typically meets working in a city,"},{"time":574997,"text":"where they say, \"Oh, that road\nis too crowded, we need to add a lane.\""},{"time":578487,"text":"So you add a lane, and the traffic comes,"},{"time":580671,"text":"and they say, \"See, I told you\nwe needed that lane.\""},{"time":583152,"text":"This applies both to highways\nand to city streets if they're congested."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586968,"text":"But the amazing thing\nabout most American cities that I work in,"},{"time":590027,"text":"the more typical cities,"},{"time":591340,"text":"is that they have a lot of streets\nthat are actually oversized"},{"time":594396,"text":"for the congestion\nthey're currently experiencing."},{"time":596827,"text":"This was the case in Oklahoma City,"},{"time":598574,"text":"when the mayor came running\nto me, very upset,"},{"time":601117,"text":"because they were named\nin Prevention Magazine"},{"time":603545,"text":"the worst city for pedestrians\nin the entire country."},{"time":606722,"text":"Now that can't possibly be true,"},{"time":608452,"text":"but it certainly is enough\nto make a mayor do something about it."},{"time":611605,"text":"We did a walkability study,"},{"time":612938,"text":"and what we found, looking\nat the car counts on the street --"},{"time":616297,"text":"these are 3,000-, 4,000-, 7,000-car counts"},{"time":619996,"text":"and we know that two lanes\ncan handle 10,000 cars per day."},{"time":623967,"text":"Look at these numbers --\nthey're all near or under 10,000 cars,"},{"time":628648,"text":"and these were the streets\nthat were designated"},{"time":631246,"text":"in the new downtown plan"},{"time":633482,"text":"to be four lanes to six lanes wide."},{"time":636140,"text":"So you had a fundamental disconnect\nbetween the number of lanes"},{"time":639409,"text":"and the number of cars\nthat wanted to use them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641675,"text":"So it was my job to redesign\nevery street in the downtown"},{"time":645614,"text":"from curb face to curb face,"},{"time":647373,"text":"and we did it for 50 blocks of streets,"},{"time":649399,"text":"and we're rebuilding it now."},{"time":650780,"text":"So a typical oversized street to nowhere"},{"time":653844,"text":"is being narrowed, and now\nunder construction,"},{"time":656068,"text":"and the project is half done."},{"time":657732,"text":"The typical street like this, you know,"},{"time":659747,"text":"when you do that,\nyou find room for medians."},{"time":663217,"text":"You find room for bike lanes."},{"time":665223,"text":"We've doubled the amount\nof on-street parking."},{"time":667414,"text":"We've added a full bike network\nwhere one didn't exist before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671387,"text":"But not everyone has the money\nthat Oklahoma City has,"},{"time":674658,"text":"because they have an extraction\neconomy that's doing quite well."},{"time":677766,"text":"The typical city is more\nlike Cedar Rapids,"},{"time":679842,"text":"where they have an all four-lane\nsystem, half one-way system."},{"time":683856,"text":"And it's a little hard to see,"},{"time":685329,"text":"but what we've done -- what we're doing;\nit's in process right now,"},{"time":688637,"text":"it's in engineering right now --"},{"time":690265,"text":"is turning an all four-lane\nsystem, half one-way"},{"time":694080,"text":"into an all two-lane system, all two-way,"},{"time":697681,"text":"and in so doing, we're adding\n70 percent more on-street parking,"},{"time":700946,"text":"which the merchants love,"},{"time":702329,"text":"and it protects the sidewalk."},{"time":703773,"text":"That parking makes the sidewalk safe,"},{"time":705559,"text":"and we're adding a much more\nrobust bicycle network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709261,"text":"Then the lanes themselves.\nHow wide are they?"},{"time":711866,"text":"That's really important."},{"time":713100,"text":"The standards have changed\nsuch that, as Andr√©s Duany says,"},{"time":716290,"text":"the typical road\nto a subdivision in America"},{"time":718408,"text":"allows you to see\nthe curvature of the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720624,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":721687,"text":"This is a subdivision\noutside of Washington from the 1960s."},{"time":724956,"text":"Look very carefully\nat the width of the streets."},{"time":727301,"text":"This is a subdivision from the 1980s."},{"time":729432,"text":"1960s, 1980s."},{"time":731091,"text":"The standards have changed\nto such a degree"},{"time":733139,"text":"that my old neighborhood of South Beach,"},{"time":735116,"text":"when it was time to fix the street\nthat wasn't draining properly,"},{"time":738299,"text":"they had to widen it\nand take away half our sidewalk,"},{"time":740867,"text":"because the standards were wider."},{"time":742630,"text":"People go faster on wider streets."},{"time":746109,"text":"People know this."},{"time":747290,"text":"The engineers deny it,\nbut the citizens know it,"},{"time":750440,"text":"so that in Birmingham, Michigan,\nthey fight for narrower streets."},{"time":754290,"text":"Portland, Oregon, famously walkable,"},{"time":756836,"text":"instituted its \"Skinny Streets\" program\nin its residential neighborhood."},{"time":760405,"text":"We know that skinny streets are safer."},{"time":762279,"text":"The developer Vince Graham,\nin his project I'On,"},{"time":765349,"text":"which we worked on in South Carolina,"},{"time":767189,"text":"he goes to conferences and he shows\nhis amazing 22-foot roads."},{"time":771128,"text":"These are two-way roads,\nvery narrow rights of way,"},{"time":773565,"text":"and he shows this well-known philosopher,"},{"time":775588,"text":"who said, \"Broad is the road\nthat leads to destruction ..."},{"time":778482,"text":"narrow is the road that leads to life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":780607,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":782691,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":785084,"text":"This plays very well in the South."}]},{"cues":[{"time":787167,"text":"Now: bicycles."},{"time":789929,"text":"Bicycles and bicycling\nare the current revolution underway"},{"time":794435,"text":"in only some American cities."},{"time":796142,"text":"But where you build it, they come."},{"time":797807,"text":"As a planner, I hate to say that,\nbut the one thing I can say"},{"time":801840,"text":"is that bicycle population\nis a function of bicycle infrastructure."},{"time":805991,"text":"I asked my friend Tom Brennan\nfrom Nelson\\Nygaard in Portland"},{"time":809430,"text":"to send me some pictures\nof the Portland bike commute."},{"time":812034,"text":"He sent me this. I said,\n\"Was that bike to work day?\""},{"time":814566,"text":"He said, \"No, that was Tuesday.\""},{"time":816235,"text":"When you do what Portland did and spend\nmoney on bicycle infrastructure --"},{"time":821223,"text":"New York City has doubled the number\nof bikers in it several times now"},{"time":825468,"text":"by painting these bright green lanes."},{"time":827529,"text":"Even automotive cities\nlike Long Beach, California:"},{"time":831119,"text":"vast uptick in the number of bikers\nbased on the infrastructure."},{"time":835222,"text":"And of course, what really does it,"},{"time":836937,"text":"if you know 15th Street\nhere in Washington, DC --"},{"time":839337,"text":"please meet Rahm Emanuel's\nnew bike lanes in Chicago,"},{"time":842338,"text":"the buffered lane, the parallel parking\npulled off the curb,"},{"time":845740,"text":"the bikes between the parked\ncars and the curb --"},{"time":849766,"text":"these mint cyclists."},{"time":851711,"text":"If, however, as in Pasadena,\nevery lane is a bike lane,"},{"time":855286,"text":"then no lane is a bike lane."},{"time":857271,"text":"And this is the only bicyclist\nthat I met in Pasadena, so ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860407,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":862036,"text":"The parallel parking I mentioned --"},{"time":863751,"text":"it's an essential barrier of steel"},{"time":865397,"text":"that protects the curb and pedestrians\nfrom moving vehicles."},{"time":869207,"text":"This is Ft. Lauderdale;\none side of the street, you can park,"},{"time":872827,"text":"the other side of the street, you can't."},{"time":874803,"text":"This is happy hour on the parking side."},{"time":876852,"text":"This is sad hour on the other side."},{"time":879567,"text":"And then the trees themselves\nslow cars down."},{"time":882580,"text":"They move slower when trees\nare next to the road,"},{"time":884890,"text":"and, of course, sometimes\nthey slow down very quickly."},{"time":888119,"text":"All the little details --\nthe curb return radius."},{"time":891095,"text":"Is it one foot or is it 40 feet?"},{"time":892781,"text":"How swoopy is that curb to determine\nhow fast the car goes"},{"time":896251,"text":"and how much room you have to cross."},{"time":897990,"text":"And then I love this,\nbecause this is objective journalism."},{"time":901436,"text":"\"Some say the entrance to CityCenter\nis not inviting to pedestrians.\""},{"time":905539,"text":"When every aspect\nof the landscape is swoopy,"},{"time":908021,"text":"is aerodynamic, is stream-form geometrics,"},{"time":910718,"text":"it says: \"This is a vehicular place.\""},{"time":913059,"text":"So no one detail, no one speciality,\ncan be allowed to set the stage."},{"time":918158,"text":"And here, you know, this street:"},{"time":919746,"text":"yes, it will drain within a minute\nof the hundred-year storm,"},{"time":923662,"text":"but this poor woman\nhas to mount the curb every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926478,"text":"So then quickly, the comfortable walk\nhas to do with the fact"},{"time":929448,"text":"that all animals seek, simultaneously,\nprospect and refuge."},{"time":934425,"text":"We want to be able to see our predators,"},{"time":936549,"text":"but we also want to feel\nthat our flanks are covered."},{"time":939092,"text":"And so we're drawn to places\nthat have good edges,"},{"time":941607,"text":"and if you don't supply the edges,\npeople won't want to be there."},{"time":944959,"text":"What's the proper ratio\nof height to width?"},{"time":947122,"text":"Is it one to one? Three to one?"},{"time":948921,"text":"If you get beyond one to six,\nyou're not very comfortable anymore."},{"time":952730,"text":"You don't feel enclosed."},{"time":954073,"text":"Now, six to one in Salzburg\ncan be perfectly delightful."},{"time":957242,"text":"The opposite of Salzburg is Houston."},{"time":960487,"text":"The point being the parking lot\nis the principal problem here."},{"time":964111,"text":"However, missing teeth, those empty lots\ncan be issues as well,"},{"time":967710,"text":"and if you have a missing corner\nbecause of an outdated zoning code,"},{"time":970979,"text":"then you could have a missing nose\nin your neighborhood."},{"time":973911,"text":"That's what we had in my neighborhood."},{"time":975772,"text":"This was the zoning code that said\nI couldn't build on that site."},{"time":978872,"text":"As you may know, Washington, DC\nis now changing its zoning"},{"time":982623,"text":"to allow sites like this\nto become sites like this."},{"time":985777,"text":"We needed a lot of variances to do that."},{"time":987967,"text":"Triangular houses\ncan be interesting to build,"},{"time":990275,"text":"but if you get one built,\npeople generally like it."},{"time":993001,"text":"So you've got to fill those missing noses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995478,"text":"And then, finally, the interesting walk:"},{"time":997460,"text":"signs of humanity."},{"time":999156,"text":"We are among the social primates."},{"time":1000995,"text":"Nothing interests us more\nthan other people."},{"time":1003207,"text":"We want signs of people."},{"time":1004725,"text":"So the perfect one-to-one ratio,\nit's a great thing."},{"time":1007752,"text":"This is Grand Rapids,\na very walkable city,"},{"time":1009980,"text":"but nobody walks on this street"},{"time":1011646,"text":"that connects the two\nbest hotels together,"},{"time":1013781,"text":"because if on the left,\nyou have an exposed parking deck,"},{"time":1018173,"text":"and on the right,\nyou have a conference facility"},{"time":1020681,"text":"that was apparently designed\nin admiration for that parking deck,"},{"time":1024134,"text":"then you don't attract that many people."},{"time":1026665,"text":"Mayor Joe Riley, in his 10th term,\nMayor of Charleston, South Carolina,"},{"time":1030663,"text":"taught us it only takes\n25 feet of building"},{"time":1032864,"text":"to hide 250 feet of garage."},{"time":1035182,"text":"This one I call the Chia Pet Garage.\nIt's in South Beach."},{"time":1037926,"text":"That active ground floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039394,"text":"I want to end with this project\nthat I love to show."},{"time":1042137,"text":"It's by Meleca Architects.\nIt's in Columbus, Ohio."},{"time":1044672,"text":"To the left is the convention center\nneighborhood, full of pedestrians."},{"time":1048386,"text":"To the right is the Short North\nneighborhood -- ethnic,"},{"time":1051074,"text":"great restaurants,\ngreat shops, struggling."},{"time":1053795,"text":"It wasn't doing very well\nbecause this was the bridge,"},{"time":1056373,"text":"and no one was walking\nfrom the convention center"},{"time":1058864,"text":"into that neighborhood."},{"time":1060237,"text":"Well, when they rebuilt the highway,\nthey added an extra 80 feet to the bridge."},{"time":1064554,"text":"Sorry -- they rebuilt the bridge\nover the highway."},{"time":1067052,"text":"The city paid 1.9 million dollars,"},{"time":1069449,"text":"they gave the site to a developer,"},{"time":1071719,"text":"the developer built this"},{"time":1073134,"text":"and now the Short North\nhas come back to life."},{"time":1075477,"text":"And everyone says, the newspapers,\nnot the planning magazines,"},{"time":1078717,"text":"the newspapers say\nit's because of that bridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080962,"text":"So that's it. That's the general\ntheory of walkability."},{"time":1083606,"text":"Think about your own cities."},{"time":1085650,"text":"Think about how you can apply it."},{"time":1088091,"text":"You've got to do all four things at once."},{"time":1090069,"text":"So find those places\nwhere you have most of them"},{"time":1092402,"text":"and fix what you can,"},{"time":1094331,"text":"fix what still needs fixing\nin those places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097039,"text":"I really appreciate your attention,"},{"time":1098831,"text":"and thank you for coming today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101531,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}